768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-2.png?resize=1536%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-2.png?resize=2048%2C2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-2.png?resize=70%2C70&amp;ssl=1 70w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-2.png?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-attachment-id=\"12176\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/sins-invalid-justice-means-a-disability-centered-response-to-covid-19\/sins-invalid-3\/\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?fit=2100%2C2100&amp;ssl=1\" data-orig-size=\"2100,2100\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"Social Distancing is Disability Justice\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"&lt;p&gt;Art: Rafi Darrow&lt;\/p&gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?fit=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?fit=800%2C800&amp;ssl=1\" width=\"800\" height=\"800\" data-id=\"12176\"  src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=800%2C800&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"A blue background with a pattern of delicate line-drawings of plants, overlaid with orange blocks with blue text that reads: \u201cSocial Distancing is Disability Justice.\u201d Art by Rafi Darrow.\" class=\"wp-image-12176\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?w=2100&amp;ssl=1 2100w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=1536%2C1536&amp;ssl=1 1536w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=2048%2C2048&amp;ssl=1 2048w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?resize=70%2C70&amp;ssl=1 70w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/disabilitycovidchronicles.nyu.edu\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/sins-invalid-3.jpg?w=1600&amp;ssl=1 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><figcaption>Art: Rafi Darrow<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These images were posted by Sins Invalid on March 19, 2020, early in the pandemic on a page entitled <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sinsinvalid.org\/news-1\/2020\/3\/19\/social-distancing-and-crip-survival-a-disability-centered-response-to-covid-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Social Distancing and Crip Survival: A Disability-Centered Response to Covid-19<\/a>. As a disability justice organization, Sins Invalid was among the first organizations to highlight the ways in which the Covid-19 pandemic would both uniquely impact disabled people and to highlight the resources and resilience that crip and chronically-ill communities could offer during a time of collective crisis, as <a href=\"https:\/\/www.sinsinvalid.org\/news-1\/2020\/3\/19\/social-distancing-and-crip-survival-a-disability-centered-response-to-covid-19\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">they wrote<\/a>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>In some ways, it isn\u2019t so different from how many of us live our lives every day as crips, with long stretches of time at home, limited access to community or touch or social engagement, engaging in mutual aid, sharing meds &amp; home remedies. Many of us who are immunocompromised\/suppressed or chemically injured have had to think about how many people we will encounter on any given day, what that will expose us to, and how it could impact our health. It\u2019s an irony that the whole world is talking about and problem solving with us now. It\u2019s painful that able bodied\/minded people evidence their ableist privilege with frustration that air travel is inaccessible, that their schedules are impacted by others\u2019 schedules, that they can\u2019t do their normal social routines\u2026 Welcome to our world!<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p>This <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.sinsinvalid.org\/news-1\/2020\/3\/19\/social-distancing-and-crip-survival-a-disability-centered-response-to-covid-19\" target=\"_blank\">post<\/a> by Sins Invalid also included early practical safety and survival tips from members, alongside links to mutual aid resources and poetry.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2014 Faye Ginsburg &amp; Harris Kornstein<\/p>\n","prote